[{"question":"How do you feel about this extraordinary mayhem erupting around you, your story, this movie?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s a bit surreal for sure because, I mean, I think controversial more than notorious.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":32,"aSentId":33},{"question":"What is the real message you want to get out?","answer":"Well, I mean, I guess for me, I -- it\u0027s important that the movie is viewed the right way certainly as a cautionary tale.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":38,"aSentId":39},{"question":"And what did make you feel like to see DiCaprio do that?","answer":"It was amazing.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":86,"aSentId":87},{"question":"How much time did you spend with Leo DiCaprio?","answer":"I spent a lot.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":94,"aSentId":95},{"question":"Like what?","answer":"You know, countless hours, you know, hundreds of hours.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":96,"aSentId":97},{"question":"Hundreds of hours in his company?","answer":"Yeah, or hundred plus hours.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":98,"aSentId":99},{"question":"And how did you find him and how did he find you when you were just interacting together?","answer":"Oh, either, you know, by telephone in my house or his house or out somewhere.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":100,"aSentId":101},{"question":"When you watched the movie, what did you feel about the reality because only you would know really?","answer":"You know it was shocking.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":111,"aSentId":112},{"question":"In a good or bad way?","answer":"In a -- in a good way.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":114,"aSentId":115},{"question":"A female employee shaved her head for $10,000 in front of the paying morbid (ph) stuff, true?","answer":"True.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":134,"aSentId":135},{"question":"To get breast implant, she shaved her head for $10,000?","answer":"Yes, yes and if they -- I guess that the philosophy was, you know, her hair will grow back and then it would all be perfect in six months.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":139,"aSentId":140},{"question":"$50?","answer":"Well, you become numb and that\u0027s what happened with insanity and all the sort of stuff that you do where what seems amazing at first becomes complex after a while.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":148,"aSentId":149},{"question":"Did that happen?","answer":"I wasn\u0027t there at that time.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":160,"aSentId":161},{"question":"But you heard it happened?","answer":"After I left, yes, yes.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":163,"aSentId":164},{"question":"Your number two portrayed in the movie by Jonah Hill ate a live goldfish that belong to a Sratton Oakmont, the firm employee, did that happen?","answer":"It happened.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":176,"aSentId":177},{"question":"You saw him do that?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":178,"aSentId":179},{"question":"So the real-life guy is who really?","answer":"It\u0027s a guy named Danny.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":182,"aSentId":183},{"question":"But did Danny eat the goldfish?","answer":"He ate the goldfish though, yes, and he has publicly admitted that and ...","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":186,"aSentId":187},{"question":"It kind of nadir (ph) of croaking (ph) excess, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":190,"aSentId":191},{"question":"It\u0027s about who can go the furthest?","answer":"I think it -- I think that sort of behavior isn\u0027t just endemic to Wall Street.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":196,"aSentId":197},{"question":"Did you have a chimpanzee in the office handing out mail?","answer":"Not mail because they have like -- people had pets in the office.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":200,"aSentId":201},{"question":"You kind of thinking this is perfectly normal?","answer":"ELFORT: I don\u0027t know.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":205,"aSentId":206},{"question":"Can you give me a clue?","answer":"It had to do with in act of sexual deprave view.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":216,"aSentId":217},{"question":"Do you?","answer":"No.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":235,"aSentId":236},{"question":"Well, how would you categorize it?","answer":"A bit of embarrassment, and you know, putting on brave face maybe.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":246,"aSentId":247},{"question":"Do you feel shame?","answer":"Not -- it\u0027s not -- shame is the wrong word.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":249,"aSentId":250},{"question":"When was it you realized you have this ability to sell?","answer":"The first time is -- it really started in the meat business.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":266,"aSentId":267},{"question":"They want a dental school and you bail?","answer":"Yeah, I bailed.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":272,"aSentId":273},{"question":"Because I have apparently guys and you couldn\u0027t make -- you couldn\u0027t rich too, right?","answer":"I, yeah -- I\u0027ve really, you know, I always want to be rich.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":274,"aSentId":275},{"question":"You actually made yourself bankrupt?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":293,"aSentId":294},{"question":"Do you think you missed this?","answer":"And I\u0027m like, \"This is it.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":324,"aSentId":325},{"question":"When you say over meaning was it -- didn\u0027t the firm went on?","answer":"Yes, the firm.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":330,"aSentId":331},{"question":"They cure cancer?","answer":"Besides they cure cancer that\u0027s the problem.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":360,"aSentId":361},{"question":"And what do you realize in that moment?","answer":"Well, you know, one of the important distinctions I think is the people to know you, especially young people, is that in the movie when I walk into the firm and I get my first look at it, and I sit down.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":371,"aSentId":372},{"question":"Is that what happened in real life?","answer":"No, not quite.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":391,"aSentId":392},{"question":"When did you realize it wasn\u0027t what it seemed?","answer":"About two -- I would say about a month in -- I totally got what\u0027s going on.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":405,"aSentId":406},{"question":"And is that the ethical moment for you when you crossed the line?","answer":"It was -- there was a series of moments.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":407,"aSentId":408},{"question":"When it became as big firm, Stratton Oakmont, and you were making millions and millions and millions, how much of it do you think -- looking back of it, and be completely honest here because you have been about many things, how much of it was legal and how much of it was illegal?","answer":"I would say 90 percent was legal in terms of the data it operates, 95 probably, but the five percent was incredibly destructive, and disgusting, and poisoned, everything else.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":416,"aSentId":417},{"question":"And you knew that was all happening?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":418,"aSentId":419},{"question":"Why did you become this art criminal?","answer":"Well, I think that what happened was is that when you get into this section of Wall Street, it\u0027s very easy just sort of rationalizing what you\u0027re doing and I rationalized each of my actions one step at a time.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":432,"aSentId":433},{"question":"And what\u0027s the easy answer?","answer":"Is that they didn\u0027t do it.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":438,"aSentId":439},{"question":"Did you lose your soul completely?","answer":"You know, I think that\u0027s -- it\u0027s hard to say because I think that I got to a point in my life where I was probably about as awful as a person as I was capable of being and still walking around.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":441,"aSentId":442},{"question":"Are you surprised more people in Wall Street haven\u0027t gone to prison since the financial crash that we all went through?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":445,"aSentId":446},{"question":"As of now, you\u0027ve paid back how much?","answer":"About 12.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":452,"aSentId":453},{"question":"Do you have any expectation or hope you\u0027ll ever get to pay them all back?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":455,"aSentId":456},{"question":"Is that not right anymore?","answer":"That\u0027s not right.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":461,"aSentId":462},{"question":"Was there ever the case?","answer":"Yes, for I was on probation.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":464,"aSentId":465},{"question":"But are you continuing to do that?","answer":"I\u0027m giving 100 percent of both books, everything, and the movie.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":468,"aSentId":469},{"question":"Why is that not true?","answer":"Because we we\u0027re calling rich people.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":476,"aSentId":477},{"question":"What?","answer":"That you were deliberately...","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":492,"aSentId":493},{"question":"Well, some of them did, right?","answer":"I don\u0027t know anyone who lost their life savings.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":505,"aSentId":506},{"question":"... in some cases, having their lives completely turned upside down?","answer":"I think it\u0027s terrible.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":512,"aSentId":513},{"question":"Have you met one of your victims?","answer":"I have not.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":515,"aSentId":516},{"question":"Why not?","answer":"No one just sought me out.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":517,"aSentId":518},{"question":"Why haven\u0027t you sought them out?","answer":"You know, I don\u0027t want to intrude anybody\u0027s life and you know...","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":519,"aSentId":520},{"question":"But have you ever seen them as human beings or it\u0027s part of the issue with the kind of culture that we see in the movie that actually in the end you become suddenly dehumanized?","answer":"Oh Piers, I think it\u0027s a very good point you\u0027re bringing up.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":539,"aSentId":540},{"question":"If I found a few of your victims, would you come and see them?","answer":"If you found them, oh yeah, sure I would.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":553,"aSentId":554},{"question":"Is that what you\u0027re saying?","answer":"Possibly.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":557,"aSentId":558},{"question":"What about somebody losing half their life savings like the guy I read out, Peter Springsteel?","answer":"Well, again I..","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":569,"aSentId":570},{"question":"My parents?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":581,"aSentId":582},{"question":"What else did she say to you?","answer":"No judgment.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":591,"aSentId":592},{"question":"Really?","answer":"No.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":593,"aSentId":594},{"question":"No criticism?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":595,"aSentId":596},{"question":"Your father, what did he say?","answer":"Similar.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":598,"aSentId":599},{"question":"How best to deal with the feelings you may have of the old Jordan Belfort?","answer":"You know it\u0027s -- I think for me I\u0027m in a place in my life right now where my -- the business I\u0027m in right now where I go around the world doing seminars, and sales training, and motivations, stuff like that, and entrepreneurship -- I know in my heart that what I\u0027m doing is pure and it\u0027s great and it\u0027s empowering.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":622,"aSentId":623},{"question":"And as scene in the movie, this memorable scene where Leo DiCaprio taking too many quellos (ph) and just basically disintegrating before our very eyes which happened, right?","answer":"An incredible acting.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":643,"aSentId":644},{"question":"Was it the balloon going up, being arrested, was it the court case, was it going to prison, was it the first night in prison, what was the absolute lowest moment for you?","answer":"I think the lowest moment for me was not getting arrested.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":657,"aSentId":658},{"question":"Bad father?","answer":"I know I was an amazing father and I\u0027m proud of that.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":670,"aSentId":671},{"question":"Always an amazing father?","answer":"Oh, I mean listen I had a -- I got sober when my daughter was three and my son was one.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":673,"aSentId":674},{"question":"What\u0027s your relationship with them like now?","answer":"I was really, really close.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":677,"aSentId":678},{"question":"What did they think of the movie?","answer":"It was -- and it\u0027s good question.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":679,"aSentId":680},{"question":"Did you hit her at all?","answer":"Well, we had a struggle on the stairs.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":683,"aSentId":684},{"question":"When you took your ex-wife and your kid to the cinema to watch the movie, you\u0027re about to finish that story, how did they feel?","answer":"Obviously, I mean look my children have seen me come back from jail and all that to build this new life.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":698,"aSentId":699},{"question":"A tweet here from Sam Gustin in Time Magazine, a critical unanswered question comment on depiction that he remained on SCC deal, why do you that if true?","answer":"It\u0027s not true.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":716,"aSentId":717},{"question":"But it wasn\u0027t about that?","answer":"It changed -- it wasn\u0027t like that really.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":723,"aSentId":724},{"question":"Did you feel guilt about all the people he went to prison because you basically wiped yourself up and ratted on him?","answer":"Not Steve Madden at all.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":731,"aSentId":732},{"question":"Have you spoken to him since?","answer":"I haven\u0027t.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":735,"aSentId":736},{"question":"How do you feel about that now?","answer":"It\u0027s a good question and there\u0027s two sides to that coin because, you know, what do you -- the part of that says, \"Well, I\u0027m supposed to do the right thing and be an upstanding citizen and as crimes committed I should help bring those people to justice.\"","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":740,"aSentId":741},{"question":"Could you do the same again?","answer":"I think the way I split that was in the movie.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":746,"aSentId":747},{"question":"No regrets?","answer":"It\u0027s not that I don\u0027t have regrets, of course I have regrets about it but I think I made -- I know that I made the right decision morally and unethically.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":757,"aSentId":758},{"question":"So the best thing to say is I would say to you, \"Piers, how long have you been in the market for a pen?","answer":"I\u0027m on the pen for three months.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":767,"aSentId":768},{"question":"I see you\u0027re looking for a pen for three months now?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":769,"aSentId":770},{"question":"And what type of pens do you typically use when you use a pen?","answer":"I like a nice easy to use ballpoint pen or something.","docId":"140124pmt","qSentId":772,"aSentId":773}]